# Model family ranking — spec 0.3.
#
# One model-family id-prefix per line, in preference order (best first). The
# model-select.sh helper enumerates /v1/models, groups results by these
# prefixes, picks the highest version within the highest-ranked family the
# account has access to, and prefers the largest-context variant when the
# listing distinguishes by max_input_tokens.
#
# Add a brand-new family by inserting a line above its weaker peers. The
# unknown-newer heuristic catches a higher version inside an already-listed
# family even when this file hasn't been touched, so the only edits this
# file requires are net-new families (e.g. when Anthropic ships a new tier
# above Fable).
#
# Comments and blank lines are ignored. Whitespace is trimmed.

# Tier 1: Fable family — Claude's most capable in-cycle model (per
# /docs/en/model-config: "the most capable model in Claude Code"). Listed
# first so an account with Fable access always selects Fable.
claude-fable

# Tier 2: Mythos family — Fable's stablemate per the Fable launch notes.
claude-mythos

# Tier 3: Opus family — current default for the Anthropic API on Max,
# Team Premium, Enterprise pay-as-you-go.
claude-opus

# Tier 4: Sonnet family — daily-coding default on Pro / Team Standard /
# Enterprise subscription seats.
claude-sonnet

# Tier 5: Haiku family — fast/cheap, used here only when nothing above
# is available to the account.
claude-haiku
